#28. Get mean, standard deviation, median and interquartile range of averageRating, numVotes and runtimeMinutes variable of training and testing data and interpret them carefully
#calculate summary for train datasheet
train_summary<- train_data %>%
  summarize(
   avg_rating_mean = mean(train_data$averageRating),
   avg_numvote_mean = mean(train_data$numVotes),
   avg_runtime_mean = mean(as.numeric(train_data$runtimeMinutes)),
  #median
  avg_rating_median = median(train_data$averageRating),
  avg_numvote_median =median(train_data$numVotes),
  avg_runtime_medain = median(as.numeric(train_data$runtimeMinutes)),
  #Standard deviation
  avg_rating_sd = sd(train_data$averageRating),
  avg_numvote_sd =sd(train_data$numVotes),
  avg_runtime_sd =sd(as.numeric(train_data$runtimeMinutes)),
  #Inetrquartile range
  avg_rating_iqr = sd(train_data$averageRating),
  avg_numvote_iqr = sd(train_data$numVotes),
  avg_runtime_Iqr = sd(as.numeric(train_data$runtimeMinutes)),
  )
